<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 26 at 6:45PM CST  by NWS San Angelo</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTHWESTERN BROWN AND
NORTHEASTERN COLEMAN COUNTIES THROUGH 730 PM CST...
At 645 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Burkett, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Byrds, Burkett, May, and Cross Cut.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
